    <item>
      <title>Marina Returns - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACCF Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/02/01/marina-returns/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/02/01/marina-returns/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 02 Feb 2025 04:28:56 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-13240" class="post-13240 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Marina Returns&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Today, I found a house in the same spot where Roscoe lived (until last week). When I went inside, I was very pleased to find Marina the octopus! 🐙&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RUU_8144-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Marina: Well, it's nice to meet you. I'm new here, so I'm sorry if I seem a little frazzles. My name is Marina." class="wp-image-13243" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I&amp;#8217;ve always liked Marina. She has lived here before, of course. In fact, she moved into Forest in &lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2016/02/14/valentines-day-2016/"&gt;February of 2016&lt;/a&gt; as well! Welcome back, Marina!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I ran into Big Top over by Able Sisters, and he said that the first of every month is going to be Hide-and-Seek Day!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RUU_8145-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Big Top: You know what I just decided? The 1st of every month is gonna be Hide-and-Seek Day!" class="wp-image-13244" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Of course, he&amp;#8217;s not going to stick to that schedule. But we did play today! He gave me ten minutes to find him, Punchy, and Ruby&amp;#8230;and I found Ruby almost immediately. She was behind a coconut tree, between Marina&amp;#8217;s new house and Scott&amp;#8217;s house.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RUU_8146-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Ruby: Oh wow! You totally found me!" class="wp-image-13245" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Three minutes later, I found Punchy behind a tree on the cliff, south of Able Sisters.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="280" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/accf-punchy-rat-sm-150x84.jpg" alt="Punchy: Not to be a rat, but you have one of us left to find. So, hurry up and get to it." class="wp-image-13246" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;And with four minutes remaining on the timer, I found Big Top near the museum. He gave me a mini alloid for winning the game, and he complimented me on my X-ray vision. 🩻&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RUU_8147-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Big Top: We're no match for you and your X-ray vision, bud!" class="wp-image-13247" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Right afterwards, I spoke with Ruby and she complained about the lack of events lately. She said it was &amp;#8220;SOOOOO boring.&amp;#8221; It was as if she didn&amp;#8217;t know she just played a game of hide-and-seek. 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Later on, I played again to attend K.K. Slider&amp;#8217;s Saturday night show. He performed one of my favorites for me: &amp;#8220;Two Days Ago.&amp;#8221; 👍&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RUU_8148-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="K.K.: All right, get ready to dig the riffs on this ditty: Two Days Ago." class="wp-image-13248" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I posted my latest ACCF video yesterday; check out City Folk Moments #24:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"&gt;&lt;div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"&gt; &lt;iframe loading="lazy" title="ACCF - City Folk Moments #24 (Animal Crossing)" width="660" height="371" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/w4YFsfO-wsg?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;    &lt;p&gt;And last but not least, here are a few other quick notes about today&amp;#8217;s session:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;I shot down a balloon present that contained a brick block. &lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Felicity was sick with a cold, so I gave her some medicine.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;I obtained four gyroids today (including the one from Big Top), but none were ones that I needed for Brewster.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;My buddy Butch was in the city, so I had a little chat with him. 🙂&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/02/01/marina-returns/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-02-01T23:28:56-05:00"&gt;February 1, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-02-01T23:30:29-05:00"&gt;February 1, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RUU_8144-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Island Life 101 - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Horizons Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/02/01/island-life-101/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/02/01/island-life-101/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 02 Feb 2025 02:58:56 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8581" class="post-8581 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Island Life 101&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Monday, June was sitting near my fountain structure (near the shop) as Bob was walking by&amp;#8230;on his way to work at the diner, apparently. 😆 Either that, or I just liked this screen grab. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/bobjune-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="June looks back up at me, while Bob walks by." class="wp-image-8585" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Wednesday was the Lunar New Year, and each of my villagers mentioned it. But there was no proper in-game event for the occasion.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/rio-lunar-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Rio: Haaaaaappyyyy Lunar New Year! I, you know, LOVE holidays. So I'm ALL about this New Year's sequel!" class="wp-image-8586" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Rio is sitting on the ground here; she&amp;#8217;s not as short as she looks.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Buzz the eagle was camping at the campsite; I currently have him in my GameCube town. He&amp;#8217;s pretty cool, but I did not ask him to move in.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/buzz-camper-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Buzz, at the campsite: Howdy! I'm just stakin' a claim for a bit, enjoyin' the campin' life. Be seein' you around, captain!" class="wp-image-8587" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;He must be allergic to the letter G.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;On Thursday, Pascal popped up when I found a scallop in the ocean. He spoke out against the rules of grammar, and his last sentence made my brain hiccup and then melt. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/pascal-grammar-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Pascal: Grammar is just word jail, maaan. Words gotta be free. Rules that who wasn't this need, like?" class="wp-image-8588" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I&amp;#8217;d rather listen to Yoda rapping in Pig Latin than try to wrap my head around whatever Pascal just said. 😡&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Today, I decided to use a feature that was introduced in &lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2021/11/03/acnh-2-update/"&gt;Version 2.0&lt;/a&gt; that I hadn&amp;#8217;t tried out yet! It&amp;#8217;s the &amp;#8220;Island Life 101&amp;#8221; app. I redeemed 400 Nook Miles and the app was immediately installed on my NookPhone.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/101app-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="The Island Life 101 app installed on my NookPhone." class="wp-image-8589" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/island-life-101-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="I installed Island Life 101! Now I'll get lots of helpful advice and info on living here through my NookPhone." class="wp-image-8590" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But even though it installs right away, you only get tips when you start up the game. So I saved and quit, and then restarted. The tips show up during loading screens, much like the tips in recent Zelda games (and others).&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/101-loading-250x141.jpg" alt="Isabelle: You can use a music box to listen to music-box arrangements of K.K.'s songs." class="wp-image-8583" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But as the name implies, these tips are designed for beginners. One tip mentions being able to crush rocks or dig up trees by eating fruit, and another one discusses changing the flag at Resident Services. This app would&amp;#8217;ve been helpful it was available when the game first launched in 2020. By the time Version 2.0 came out in late 2021, most players already knew these things.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="139" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/101-orders-250x50.jpg" alt="Tom Nook: Orders from Nook Shopping are limited to five items per person each day. When there are a lot of things you want, please make sure to plan accordingly! Yes, yes!" class="wp-image-8584" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;It&amp;#8217;s nothing to write home about, and it was probably the least exciting part of the 2.0 update. But I guess I just wanted to cross it off my mental to-do list and get it over with. 😆 I&amp;#8217;m curious, have you all downloaded the app or no? Let me know in the comments.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Anyway, here are a few other quick notes about this week:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;On Wednesday, June was sick with a cold. I gave her some medicine, and she returned the favor by giving me a jester&amp;#8217;s cap.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;I helped out Gulliver, and he sent me my 10 millionth sombrero on Thursday.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Yesterday, I sold 35 bugs to Flick for 153,750 bells.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Tonight, K.K. performed &amp;#8220;I Love You&amp;#8221; for me, Rio, Agent S, and Louie.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I&amp;#8217;ll see you next time! Never Stop Crossing!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/02/01/island-life-101/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-02-01T21:58:56-05:00"&gt;February 1, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-02-01T22:11:00-05:00"&gt;February 1, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/bobjune-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Glute Displacer - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACWW Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/01/31/glute-displacer/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/01/31/glute-displacer/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 01 Feb 2025 04:59:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-7924" class="post-7924 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Glute Displacer&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;The flea market is coming up soon, and Drift told me that he wants to buy some new dumbbells and a Glute Displacer. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/drift-glute0-150x112.jpg" alt="Drift: I wanna buy new dumbbells and a Glute Displacer with the money I'll make!" class="wp-image-7926" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;So he said I better buy a lot from him, because Glute Displacers aren&amp;#8217;t cheap! 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/drift-glute-150x112.jpg" alt="Drift: So you better buy lots! Glute Displacers ain't cheap, y'know, brah!" class="wp-image-7925" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Especially if they have to be imported from Butt-swana. &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Wendell was in town yesterday, but I actually didn&amp;#8217;t speak with him this time. However, I liked how Booker mentioned his appearance&amp;#8230;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/booker-walrus-150x112.jpg" alt="Booker: I saw a very hungry-looking walrus come through here... At least, I think I did." class="wp-image-7927" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I love how he&amp;#8217;s not entirely sure if that large walrus he saw was real or not. What exactly is going on in his head that is making him question it? Is he afraid to turn to Copper and say &amp;#8220;Whoa, dude, did you just see a walrus with an easel and art supplies walk by just now?&amp;#8221; 😆&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Curt has still been sick this week, so I gave him some more medicine Wednesday, yesterday, and today. Get well, already! 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Outside of town hall tonight, Whitney told me that Bones picked up a harmonica. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/whitney-harmonica-150x112.jpg" alt="Whitney: Guess what? Bones picked up a harmonica!" class="wp-image-7933" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I didn&amp;#8217;t know what she was talking about at first, but she said he found it in the recycling bin. Okay, well at least that makes sense&amp;#8230;except for the fact that this game doesn&amp;#8217;t have a harmonica. Oh well. 🤷&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Tank asked me to make a delivery to Caroline, and the gift was a blue diamond top. She wasn&amp;#8217;t exactly thrilled with it.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/caroline-pinch-150x112.jpg" alt="Caroline: It sure is different... But I guess it'll do in a pinch, on my Wii." class="wp-image-7928" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I returned to Tank and told him that Caroline just thought the gift was okay. He thought it was weird that she didn&amp;#8217;t love it. But he still rewarded me with an illusion wall.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/tank-rave-150x112.jpg" alt="Tank: Not exactly a rave review... Weird, in 2025." class="wp-image-7929" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Drift told me that when times were tough, he would spend hours collecting shells and selling them to Tom Nook. But now, he&amp;#8217;s wondering what Tom Nook does with all those shells&amp;#8230;make swimming suits? 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/drift-shells1-150x112.jpg" alt="Drift: So, you think he's making swimming suits with those shells?!" class="wp-image-7930" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;That made me think of Ariel&amp;#8217;s seashell bikini in &amp;#8220;The Little Mermaid.&amp;#8221; But to my surprise, Drift said he wanted one for himself! 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/drift-shells2-150x112.jpg" alt="Drift: Man, if so, sign me up 'cuz I want one! That is so dang HOT, brah!!!" class="wp-image-7931" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;On that odd note, I think that about wraps up my week in Animal Crossing: Wild World. But as a reminder, Bright Nights takes place next week! Don&amp;#8217;t forget to check it out if you still play ACWW!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/bn-post-150x112.jpg" alt="- Bright Nights Notice - Bright Nights will start next Monday! Who will win the treasured crown of best light decorator?" class="wp-image-7932" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;See you soon!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c27d879b16e3317f0d6fa350680e5023?s=98&amp;#038;d=mm&amp;#038;r=g' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/01/31/glute-displacer/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-01-31T23:59:00-05:00"&gt;January 31, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-02-01T01:14:11-05:00"&gt;February 1, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/drift-glute0.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Sydney&amp;#039;s Sea Bass - Jeff&amp;#039;s Animal Crossing Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/01/31/sydneys-sea-bass/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/01/31/sydneys-sea-bass/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 01 Feb 2025 04:05:58 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-5882" class="post-5882 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Sydney&amp;#8217;s Sea Bass&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Today, I received a goodbye letter from Marcy in the mail. She has already bounced out of town.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/ac-marcy-out-sm-300x231.jpg" alt="Guess what, Jeff! I realize this is a little cuckoo, but I've decided to move. Have I lost it? No!!! I've just got to try to get a fresh start. I don't even know where I'm going yet! See ya! -Marcy" class="wp-image-5883" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Just south of my home acre, I found an igloo near my central ramp.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/ac-igloo2025-sm-300x231.jpg" alt="An igloo near the central ramp in Forest." class="wp-image-5884" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Genji was inside, and he told me that he just built the igloo to surprise me. But it was a lot of hard work &amp;#8220;for one beast,&amp;#8221; and he was really tired.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/ac-genji-igloo-sm-300x231.jpg" alt="Genji, falling asleep in an igloo: Just a little longer... Need sleep..." class="wp-image-5885" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;That peaceful igloo music makes me want to take a nap, too!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Over at Nookington&amp;#8217;s, there wasn&amp;#8217;t any buying or selling going on today. That&amp;#8217;s because it&amp;#8217;s the last day of the month: Raffle Day. I didn&amp;#8217;t have any raffle tickets, but I did take a quick look at the prizes.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/ac-raffle2025-sm-300x231.jpg" alt="Tom Nook, on Raffle Day: Today's a raffle day, hm? I'm not selling anything." class="wp-image-5886" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Maple has a new next-door neighbor, Bangle the tiger! Tigers seem to have particularly huge heads in this game. 😆 She seems nice, but she was not aware that igloos have already started appearing in town.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/ac-bangle-sm-300x231.jpg" alt="Bangle: Oooooh! Hey! Do you think we'll start seeing igloos in Forest soon?" class="wp-image-5887" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;When I ran into Belle, she was up to her usual tricks. She wanted me to buy a mod wall for 5,150 bells. If I&amp;#8217;m not mistaken, that&amp;#8217;s nearly five times what Tom Nook sells it for! So naturally, I declined the offer. She wasn&amp;#8217;t particularly rude about my refusal this time, but she did say that was the lowest she could go. Yeah, good luck ever selling it for that much.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/ac-belle-sell2-sm-300x231.jpg" alt="Belle: Too rich for your blood, cuddles?" class="wp-image-5888" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I found Gulliver washed up on the beach, and I woke him up. He used his infamous line that mentions the year, and I never get tired of this bit. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/ac-gulliver2025a-sm-300x231.jpg" alt="Gulliver: Yawn... What a great nap! What!? It's 2025? But that means I've been asleep for over 150..." class="wp-image-5889" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/ac-gulliver2025b-sm-300x231.jpg" alt="Gulliver: ...minutes." class="wp-image-5890" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He gave me a Lady Liberty (a model of the Statue of Liberty) for &amp;#8220;saving his life.&amp;#8221; 🗽&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Over at the wishing well, I asked Sydney for a favor. She said she wanted a pet fish, but she insisted that she was awful at fishing.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/ac-sydney-fish-sm-300x231.jpg" alt="Sydney: So, Jeff, can you please go catch a fish for me? Otherwise, I'll be forever fishless!" class="wp-image-5891" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;So I went down to the ocean and caught a red snapper. And then I went to catch &lt;em&gt;another &lt;/em&gt;fish, because I&amp;#8217;m certainly not giving her a 3,000-bell snapper. 😆 But I did catch a nice sea bass for her! 😉 She liked it, and she rewarded me with a lovely chair.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/ac-sydney-lonely-sm-300x231.jpg" alt="Sydney: I don't know if fish get lonely, but this one won't! I promise to talk to it every day, okey-dokey." class="wp-image-5892" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Her catchphrase is one she learned from Kody, &amp;#8220;okey-dokey.&amp;#8221; But just moments later, Kody asked me for a new phrase to replace &lt;em&gt;his &lt;/em&gt;&amp;#8220;okey-dokey.&amp;#8221; Maybe he didn&amp;#8217;t like the fact that Sydney was using it too. 😛 So I gave him a phrase that I once gave to Tammy in New Leaf: game cub.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/ac-kody-gamecub-sm-300x231.jpg" alt="Kody: Marry me, game cub! Whoa! That sounds awesome! I'm gonna be so popular!!!" class="wp-image-5893" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I made a stop at the post office to mail away the fossils I dug up, and then I returned home for the day. I&amp;#8217;ll see you all next month! Never Stop Crossing!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/01/31/sydneys-sea-bass/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-01-31T23:05:58-05:00"&gt;January 31, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-01-31T23:08:01-05:00"&gt;January 31, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
